        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-14T03:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-14T03:54:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90F27/7–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-14T12:00:00+03:06">July 14, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>267. Dept’s 188, July 5. King agreeable to proposal that Dept submit draft
                    bilateral civil air transport agreement for his consideration. Please forward
                    such draft.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
